BREITBART RISES FROM GRAVE TO EAT HUMAN FLESH















Conservative news publisher Andrew Breitbart has been spotted roaming through Hillside Memorial Park Cemetery. Breitbart has been reported dead since 2012.

Multiple onlookers have spotted the founder of Breitbart.com walking among the graves at Hillside Memorial Park Cemetery in Culver City, California.

I just saw Andrew Breitbart in the cemetery!!!! — Carol Mendelsohn-Slivowitz (@CarolM_S) February 24, 2017

Is that Andrew Breitbrat? I thought he was dead! — James Richards (@JRichards548) February 24, 2017

The political commentator supposedly passed five years ago from heart disease, but there are now doubts about the truth of that report.

@CarolM_S @JRichards548 He could be a zombie! — Orel Stanley (@IAmOralOrel) February 24, 2017

According to Dr. Paul Krysowski of the Santa Cruz Institute, there have been some instances of zombiness spreading in the Southwestern United States over the last decade.

Many have welcomed back the conservative pundit.

The world welcome's back Zombie Breibart! — Christian Jones (@TheRealChrisJones2) February 24, 2017

Andrew Breitbart's death was clearly a hoax by the Jew-run media!!! — Angela Dobbs (@CatWomanFan8) February 24, 2017

@Breitbart if u want some human flesh, DM me for the time & place! — Christian Jones (@TheRealChrisJones2) February 24, 2017

